# GradeFlow — AI-Powered K–12 Education Platform

**I spent 15 years teaching math.** I watched EdTech promise to help teachers and mostly deliver disappointment — clunky tools that created more work than they saved.

So I built the platform I always wished I'd had. Solo. In 47 days.

**Live:** [gradeflow.vercel.app](https://gradeflow.vercel.app)  
**Built:** Mar 9 → Apr 25, 2026 | **970 deployments** | **1,247 commits**

---

## Why This Exists

Most EdTech is designed by people who have never stood in a classroom. I've taught math to hundreds of students — in urban schools, rural schools, adult education programs. That lived experience shapes every decision in this codebase.

I didn't need user research to know that teachers are drowning in admin work. I didn't need a product manager to tell me that parent communication is a time sink. I built GradeFlow because I understood the problem from the inside.

---

## What GradeFlow Does

GradeFlow reduces teacher workload by automating the highest-value, most time-consuming tasks:

- **AI Lesson Plan Generator** — Standards-aligned, differentiated lesson plans with accessibility accommodations, powered by a 12-tier prompt system
- **Curriculum Alignment Engine** — Maps lessons to state and national standards, learning objectives, and assessment rubrics
- **AI Support Assistant** — Drafts parent communications, generates rubrics, extracts structured data from PDFs
- **Multi-Role Dashboards** — Purpose-built interfaces for teachers, students, parents, admins, and support staff
- **Real-Time Collaboration** — Shared lesson editing, class feeds, and role-aware messaging
- **Security-First Design** — 30+ RLS (Row-Level Security) policies enforcing strict database-level access control

---

## Architecture

```
┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│         React + Vite + Tailwind Frontend         │
